Phix

 

Phix song 2009

Chancel dummy vocals 2011

You have no eyes. That may be why your mouth can never call.

I pray upon your fear and hope that you will never fall.

To enter in the city of your birth, you have to roll

away the stone.


Do you know I am your mother?

Is it good I am your mother?

You just wait until your father

comes home.


You always thought that massive head was blocking your return.

The lion rears with velvet claws that hold the egg and son.

I guard the gate. Thanks to the stars, the journey has begun

for Oedipus.


Do you know I am your mother?

Is it good I am your mother?

You just wait until your father

sees this.


Serpent’s knowledge, crushed in the end, has fattened up your mind.

My wings are walls. Your flight is short. I still have all the time.

The calf was cut for feasts gone cold. I require you to try

and take questions.


Do you know I am your mother?

Is it good I am your mother?

You just wait until your father

moves on.
